{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantref\/normalform"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gets a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance that has the same value as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" and is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"trusted to be in normal form."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/normalForm","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"normalForm","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","text":"VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib15VariantProtocolPAAE10normalFormAA0B3RefVSgvp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib10VariantRefV","symbolKind":"property","role":"symbol","title":"normalForm"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/VariantProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"normalForm","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","text":"VariantRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"! { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is already trusted to be in normal form then a new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not already trusted, then it is scanned to check if it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is in normal form.  If it is found to be in normal form then it is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"marked as trusted and a new reference to it is returned.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is found not to be in normal form then a new trusted","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is created with the same value as "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The non-normal parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" will be replaced with default values which are guaranteed to be in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"normal form.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It makes sense to call this function if you’ve received "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data from untrusted sources and you want to ensure your serialized"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"output is definitely in normal form."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" is already in normal form, a new reference will be returned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which will be floating if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"text":" is floating). If it is not in normal form,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the newly created "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" will be returned with a single non-floating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reference. Typically, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_take_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called on the return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value from this function to guarantee ownership of a single non-floating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference to it."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VariantRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"VariantRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/variantref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GVariant"},{"type":"text","text":" is a variant datatype; it can contain one or more values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"along with information about the type of the values.","type":"text"}],"title":"VariantRef"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/VariantRef/normalForm":{"abstract":[{"text":"Gets a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" instance that has the same value as "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trusted to be in normal form."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef\/normalForm","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword"